note.p: Parchment paste-downs at front and back made up of two different strips each from an Ordinal (12th/13th century)and two other different(?) manuscripts. The fragment of the Ordinal at the front is from the Common of confessors and virgins, that at the back probably contains the end of the feast of Katherine and the beginning of Common of apostles. The second strip at front, not identified, contains different terms, e.g.: annosus, amor, hospes, barba with the explanations in hexameter(?); the strip at back contains conciliar statutes(?).

binding.p: Blindstamped binding by a bookbinder identified by Sten G. Lindberg as Jakob Ulfssons bookbinder, active in Uppsala in the 1490s, see The National Library of Sweden, Sten G. Lindbergs arkiv, B 13c ‘Jakob Ulfssons bokbinderi’, possibly identical to Hans bokabinder, citizen in Uppsala, see SDHK no. 33208, cf. Collijn U 387:22, Bokbindare i Sverige, 1400-talet and G. Dahlbäck, ‘Stockapenningar, tjärtunnor och beläten: Något om den senmedeltida sockenkyrkans ekonomi’, Kyrka och socken i medeltidens Sverige: en samling uppsatser, ed. O. Ferm (Stockholm, 1991), 370. Torn brown leather over wooden boards; 5 spinebands plus endbands, two hook-straps, now lost, with clasp fastenings on the upper cover.
binding.decoNote: Two frames of triple fillets forming two rectangles, in the middle separated by a border made with a roll with a foliaged staff (left cover) and another with bird (right cover); the tools in circles arranged in rectangles in corresponding pairs (the first and the last are bigger): lion and falconer, pelican and lion with a whelp, rose and rose, lion with a whelp and pelican, stag and lion;

msItem.title: Calendar
msItem.note: The calendar is almost identical to the one in Breviarium Upsalense 1496. Feasts in the Breviarium Upsalense 1496 not included here are: Ansgar, Thomas of Aquino, Compassion of Virgin Mary (6 May), Division of Apostles, Catherine of Sweden, Brynolf, Helen of Constantinople and the octave of All saints. Feasts in A 50 not in Breviarium 1496 are: Saint Alban, the Seven sleepers and the octave of saint Michael; 27 March is marked as Resurrection day.

msItem.title: Benedictions
msItem.note: Benedictions for first, second and third nocturn, for the gospel, and for virgin Mary.

note.p: This section includes memorials to virgin Mary, saints Laurentius, Ericus, Henricus amongst others, and ends with the hymn Iesu salvator saeculi verbum (AH 51.45).
